🌿 Task 5: Advanced Branching

Goal: Work on a "feature" without affecting the main code.
1. Create and Switch Branch:
```bash
git checkout -b feature-update
```
2. Modify File: Open `info.txt` and add a line about your Week 4 goals.
3. Commit & Push:
```bash
git add info.txt
git commit -m "Feature update: Enhance info.txt with additional details"
git push origin feature-update
```
4. Pull Request (PR): Go to your GitHub repo.
You’ll see a yellow bar saying "feature-update had recent pushes.
" Click Compare & pull request to merge it into `main`.

