🛡️ Bonus: SSH Authentication
Goal: Remove the need for tokens/passwords entirely.
1. Generate Key: `ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com"` (Press Enter for all prompts).
2. Copy Public Key: `cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub`
3. Add to GitHub: Paste this into *Settings > SSH and GPG keys*.
4. Update Remote:
```bash
git remote set-url origin git@github.com:<your-username>/90DaysOfDevOps.git
git push origin feature-update
```

